Words cannot express the sorrow and sadness felt by us all in the loss of a life of one of our beloved UPrep students.

As a community, we are charged to support one another through times like this. A pivotal way to do this is by providing support to our community by way of grief counseling.

We will be offering a Virtual Grief Support Group for Students and Faculty over the next 3 days (Wednesday, Thursday & Friday) We understand the importance for not only having this available for our students but staff members as well. See details below.

https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85356500732?pwd=dURpRU5Hend3QjVrQ3VTYkpVOEM1Zz09

Meeting ID: 853 5650 0732
Passcode: 2020

post_text:
And just like that, the summer is over and our graduates prepare to go onto the next stage of their lives. Whether it be College, Trade School, or the Workforce, we are extremely proud of the work you have done, and the perseverance you have shown throughout these trying times! We continue to send well wishes as you embark on your next journey.

In addition to our students experiencing Media Day, the UPREP 2020 Graduate Sendoff, and receiving their diploma, we would also like to help them get started on their way to financial responsibility and literacy by providing all of our Seniors with a scholarship to begin a Savings Account.

Please consider domnating to our GoFundMe below to contribute to this effort.

https://www.gofundme.com/f/uprep-class-of-2020

We would like to thank you for your support in viewing the documentary "1290 - Changing the Narrative", as we celebrate the 2020 Graduating Class of UPrep. We experienced a plethora of technical difficulties on yesterday, which led to us pulling both videos, which were incomplete because the upload left off many key elements of the production. The producers are working to ensure we have a smooth and efficient presentation on this evening. Please join us tonight at 8:00 for the official viewing of "1290 - Changing the Narrative", exclusively on Facebook. We also ask that you share with your networks as we celebrate our seniors together!

UPREP 2020 VIRTUAL GRADUATION COUNTDOWN

Steve Jobs once said, "If your working on something exciting that you really care about, you don't have to be pushed. The vision pulls you!"

A few months ago, with the surfacing of the Covid-19 pandemic, a Vision was Cast.

To create an experience for the UPrep Graduating Class of 2020 like never before.

On tomorrow, we will experience the first tier of that vision being fulfilled!

"1290 - Changing the Narrative"

It's Going to Be BIG!

post_text:
UPREP / SOUTHWEST REFUND UPDATE

Very thankful to share that Southwest Airlines will be refunding our students in full for the cancelled senior trip.

Mr. Miller received the news last night, and will be issuing families a full refund for total trip.

This was a total community effort to help reach the proper person at Southwest Airlines to hear our story and make the best decision with our students and families in mind.

On behalf of the administration at Uprep, we would like to say thank you to all that supported us.
text:
UPREP / SOUTHWEST REFUND UPDATE

Very thankful to share that Southwest Airlines will be refunding our students in full for the cancelled senior trip.

Mr. Miller received the news last night, and will be issuing families a full refund for total trip.

This was a total community effort to help reach the proper person at Southwest Airlines to hear our story and make the best decision with our students and families in mind.

On behalf of the administration at Uprep, we would like to say thank you to all that supported us.

post_text:
UPREP SENIOR TRIP CANCELLED
#UprepCovid19Refund
Due to COVID-19 our Uprep Senior Trip has been canceled due to executive orders and travel restrictions.

Southwest Airlines is the only company NOT giving our students a full refund. They did offer 1 Southwest Giftcard as a credit for entire group to travel at a later date, but these kids will not be able to reschedule this trip. Class of 2020 kids are not only missing their senior trip, but also Graduation ceremonies, parties, etc....

We are thankful to receive full refunds from Wyndham Grand Hotels and Resorts and Universal Studios Entertainment for our students.

At this time of struggle, we feel that these urban inner-city families should be rewarded a full refund from Southwest Airlines, just as Universal Studios and Wyndham hotels have refunded.

BUILDING MAINTENANCE CLASS AT UPREP
with Mr. Bogart

Uprep is the only All-Boys Public Charter School in Rochester that features a Career & Technical Education Center (CTE) on campus.

Students who complete the Building Maintenance Program can expect to find employment as a building maintenance mechanic, maintenance technician worker, building mechanic, apartment maintenance person or facilities worker.

FALL ENROLLMENT OPEN
Uprep is currently accepting applications for fall enrollment at Goodschoolsroc.org for boys entering grades 7-12. First come first serve.....still a few seats available in each grade.

Good Morning UPrep Families!

We are planning on handing out the remaining Chromebooks that we have tomorrow from 10:00am-2:00pm at the gym door.

1. Chromebooks will be distributed on a first come, first serve model. Supplies are limited.
2. Parents and students should come to the back gym parking lot. They can not enter the building.
3. Parents must fill out the sign out form and they will receive a copy along with a Chromebook.
4. Students with excessive absences will be given paper copies of work to do.
5. Families with more than one student at UPREP can only have 1 Chromebook.

Thank you for your support.

MEALS PROVIDED FOR ALL AGES

The Center for Youth on Monroe avenue has a food pantry that families and any youth under the age of 24 can access anytime between 9:00AM-6:00PM. They also have baby formula. There is a long list of pantries that you can get from Central Library of Rochester or call them 585-428-8168. Let’s help each other out during these difficult times. Please share!

You can call 2-1-1 Lifeline if you need to find the pantry closest to you. It's a 24/7 community resources hotline, just tell the operators what you need and where you live. The mobile food pantry program is still operating on schedule as well

Due to the local state of emergency UPREP Charter School will be closed effective Monday, March 16, 2020 until further notice.

All staff will be required to report on Monday from 8am-10am to meet with your immediate supervisor to ensure you are all set to provide home instruction to our Scholars.

School administration will continue to closely monitor the situation and notify all staff, parents, and students.
Please check emails for further information or call Uprep Charter School during business hours at 585-672-1280.

post_text:
UPREP INDOOR TRACK

Yesterday our Indoor Track and Field Team competed at R.I.T for the Section V State Qualifying Meet. Qualifiers of this meet gets to compete at the NY State Meet next weekend in Staten Island.

Notable Highlights:

MIKE CATHEY

- Finished 2nd in 55m Dash with a time of 6.48 secs

- Cathey will compete in the 55m Dash at Ocean Breeze Athlete Complex in Staten Island on Saturday, March 7th.

CHRISTON JEAN

- Finished 3rd in 55m Dash with a time of 6.56 secs

- Jean will compete in the 55m Dash at Ocean Breeze Athlete Complex in Staten Island on Saturday, March 7th.

BOYS 4x200m RELAY

- Mohamed Hussein, Mike Cathey, Josh Quinn, and Mark Rogers finished 2nd in the Boys 4x200m Relay with a time of 1:33.88.

- Boys 4x200m will compete at Ocean Breeze Athlete Complex in Staten Island on Saturday, March 7th.

Mayor Lovely A. Warren is calling eighth-grade city students
to become “Mayor for a Day,” by participating in the inaugural “If I Were Mayor” essay contest.

Eighth graders are asked to write an essay that describes how they would accomplish Mayor Warren’s mission of creating more jobs, safer and more vibrant neighborhoods, and better educational opportunities.

The winning essayist will become honorary Mayor for a day!

Email your essay to essaycontest@cityofrochester.gov by March 2, 2020.

MEET THE UPREP VARSITY BASKETBALL TEAM

The Uprep Varsity Men's Basketball Program opens the season up tonight at 6:30pm against defending NYS Federation Champs Park High School in Buffalo, NY.

Uprep finished last year as Section V Class AA runner-up, and has made it to the Sectional Championship game the last 3 years in a row. Senior returners: Fowlks, Jefferson-Edwards, and Ross, along with last season's JV standouts, and a few other additions to the Uprep basketball program offset key losses like 2019 McDonalds All-Star selection Jahki Lucas.

Meet the new 2019-2020 Uprep Basketball Team led by 2nd year head coach Demond Stewart, along with assistant Jerice Crouch.

(From left to right)
▪︎C. Jefferson-Edwards
▪︎J. Simms
▪︎N. Williams

▪︎D. Green Jr.

▪︎B. Moore Jr.
▪︎J. Matthews
▪︎A. Edwards-Ferrell
▪︎K. Ross

Buffalo, NY 14226

post_text:
UPREP CAREER & TECHNICAL EDUCATION CENTER

As a class assignment, Mr. Bogarts CTE class is currently building a shed from the ground up to provide more storage space for our school.

Keeping students engaged is a vital part of UPrep’s program, and hands-on experiences help students both inside and outside of the classroom. Young men at UPrep learn important skills in culinary arts, machining, building trades and information technology through the Career & Technical Education Center (CTE), located on the school’s campus.

Through a two-year program, students gain foundational skills that prepare them for college study or to compete for meaningful employment. Students apply these experiences during their high school careers through opportunities like the Griffin Café, a student-run restaurant that is open weekly to the public.

UPrep works with local colleges to help students gain access to programs, such as machinery, following graduation. For more information call 585-672-1280 and ask about our CTE Program.

The Uprep Varsity football team has earned the #1 Seed in the 2019 Sectional Class B Playoffs. The Griffins are looking forward to the first sectional win in Uprep history as they take on the #8 Seed Bishop Kearney Kings at 1pm at Rhinos Stadium on Saturday 10/26.

If Uprep wins the next game will be the following Saturday at 4pm at Pittsford Sutherland against the winner of Geneva and Livonia.

1. All families use gate C. The will be a swag table as well

2. All guest will set on the same side. With the empty space in between.

3. No one under the age of 18 is allowed without a guest of age. The adult must stay the entire time with the underage guest.

4. The gate will close at half time

5. No reentry

6. All guest must go through a scanner

7. Tickets are sold at the gate and it's $5.

The Gallantry is with Ken Sayres.
September 8, 2019 at 11:03 PM ·

Introducing our next Gallantry Roundtable... Raise Them Up! Will be an intentional dialogue with our men and young men together about responsibility and accountability. It's an opportunity for us to share our plights and determine ways in how we can best serve one another.

Walter Larkin and UPrep have opened their doors to host this amazing event, Michael James of Vertus High School will be our lead facilitator, he is a very dynamic and passionate brother committed to serving this community. We are going to do some good with this one 😃.

So please share this, spread the word and encourage your men and young men to be counted among us. This event is FREE FREE FREE, including food and a FREE raffle.

Big shout out to:

http://www.upreprochester.org/

AND

http://www.vertusschool.org/

Thanks,
